HEADWORD: Traipse
<hw>Traipse</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G.
<ets>trapsen</ets>, <ets>trappsen</ets>, <ets>trappen</ets>, to tread
noisily, to walk stamping. See <er>Trample</er>, <er>Trape</er>.]</ety>
<def>To walk or run about in a slatternly, careless, or thoughtless
manner.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trays</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Trais</ent>⟦br⟧
